snippet.title: How do Fish Breath Underwater? #shorts
snippet.description:
#shorts
For "HUGE" Discount on 3D Animation Course, Call: +91-99830-83303 or Click here 👉🏻 https://professorofhow.com

How do Fish Breath Underwater? #shorts 

If someone drowned your head in water, nothing will be more important for you than taking your head out for breathing. But how does a fish spends its whole life inside water? Double tap the screen and let's understand the science behind fish breathing inside water.
A fish consists of two gills on both sides of its head behind its eyes, these gills remain covered by the operculum. The breathing process in fish takes place in 2 steps.
First - The opercula and the mouth of fish both combined work as a pump, which makes water move inside the mouth of the fish through gills and takes it out of the water, this pumping is called buccal pumping.
Second - When water moves through gills, because of the numerous capillaries present in the gills, they work as a filter. These filters absorb oxygen from the water and drain the water and CO2 out of the body.
The absorbed oxygens get bonded with hemoglobin and reach the entire body and completed the breathing process.
However, the fishes like whales and dolphins cannot breathe underwater, they can remain inside the water for a long time without breathing and approach the surface of the water to inhale oxygen.

snippet.title: Sushant KC - Hawa Le
snippet.description:
I finished my show in the UK, boarded a plane, and got off in Doha. Just as I was ready to head home, I tested positive for covid and what should have been a few hours of transit ended up being a ten-day quarantine. In the boredom of isolation I opened logic on my laptop and what I ended up with was the beat to this song. I got back to Nepal and I scribbled and scribbled till I came up with the lyrics. Then I hit up my friend Nayan and asked him to tag along for a trip to Pokhara. We didn’t take any heavy equipment with us. Nor did we take a schedule. Yet these random events and decisions gave birth to this gem of a video in such a short time. Thanks to @stellarstudios.np, the most dedicated and awesome team of creators. And thanks to everyone, and every organization involved in this project. Hawa le is a vibe.

localized.title: Sushant KC - Hawa Le
localized.description:
I finished my show in the UK, boarded a plane, and got off in Doha. Just as I was ready to head home, I tested positive for covid and what should have been a few hours of transit ended up being a ten-day quarantine. In the boredom of isolation I opened logic on my laptop and what I ended up with was the beat to this song. I got back to Nepal and I scribbled and scribbled till I came up with the lyrics. Then I hit up my friend Nayan and asked him to tag along for a trip to Pokhara. We didn’t take any heavy equipment with us. Nor did we take a schedule. Yet these random events and decisions gave birth to this gem of a video in such a short time. Thanks to @stellarstudios.np, the most dedicated and awesome team of creators. And thanks to everyone, and every organization involved in this project. Hawa le is a vibe.

snippet.title: How LEECH sucks Blood? #shorts
snippet.description:
#shorts

For "HUGE" Discount on 3D Animation Course, Call: +91-99830-83303 or Click here 👉🏻 https://professorofhow.com

How do LEECH suck Blood? #shorts 

Ayurveda has explained Leech therapy, where a leech sucks your blood to cure infections. But are you aware of how a leech actually sucks your blood? Double-tap the screen to understand the process.
A leech uses its head and the sucker present on its tail to stick to a host. After sticking to the host, i.e., you, it releases an anesthetic liquid on your skin, which numbs your skin. Now it uses the 3 sharp jaws present on its head to bite you and you don't feel that bite.
After inserting its jaws into the upper layer of your skin, the leech releases a protein liquid(Hirudin) from its saliva glands. This protein prevents blood clotting in your blood, and because of this, it becomes really easy for the leech to suck your blood using rhythmic movements of its body muscles and store it in its digestive tract. After consuming around 5-15ml of your blood, the leech leaves your skin. Now, this leech could survive for 6 to 9 months with this much blood.
